{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_01EbSn5zR98yPvWjr9y89VxR","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Done. The snapshot succeeded (`\"state\": \"SUCCESS\"`).\n\n## What was wrong and what I did\n\n**Diagnosis:**\n- The S3 credentials live in the Secret `es-secure-settings`, mounted at `/mnt/secure-settings` and already loaded into each node's Elasticsearch **keystore** (`s3.client.default.access_key` / `s3.client.default.secret_key`) — the correct, secure place (no creds in `elasticsearch.yml` or env vars).\n- The StatefulSet's init container tries to install `repository-s3` as a plugin, but in ES 8.11 **repository-s3 is a built-in module**, so the plugins dir is empty and that's expected — the S3 repository type was available all along.\n\n**Actions:**\n1. `POST _nodes/reload_secure_settings` — applied the keystore S3 credentials to all 3 running nodes (S3 client credentials are reloadable, so **no pod restart was needed**).\n2. Registered repository **`minio-repo`** (type `s3`) pointing at `minio.elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local:9000`, bucket `es-backups`, with `protocol: http` and `path_style_access: true` (required for MinIO).\n3. Verified the repo across all 3 nodes, then created snapshot `snapshot-1` → **`state: SUCCESS`**.\n\nCredentials remain only in the Secret/keystore as required."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":735,"cache_read_input_tokens":34831,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":735},"output_tokens":5,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"41413d05-8b90-4cd5-ae25-a88107e6f060","uuid":"94822003-3849-4832-8e84-3be26fa4af27","request_id":"req_011CcAt2LmbVYd9cKgBwEMoc"}
